<HEADLINE> Seminar on Solar Energy Ends in Yaounde </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YAOUNDE, February 26 (Xinhua) -- The two-day seminar on solar
energy ended here this evening after discussing how to develop
and apply solar energy in the rural areas in Africa.
</P>
<P>
Minister of Scientific and Technical Research, Bava Djingoer,
urged the experts to design specific projects and concrete
recommendations on the use of solar energy especially in remote
villages.
</P>
<P>
The basic aim of the request is complementing conventional
energy with solar energy especially for lighting.
</P>
<P>
The seminar was attended by 40 participants coming from
African and European countries.
</P>
<P>
Research in solar energy and its eventual application began in
the central African country of Cameroun in 1980. 
</P>
